240 grams British Beef Mince
80 grams Sliced Mushrooms
2 unit(s) Garlic Clove
150 grams Sliced Spring Greens
50 grams Gochujang Paste
25 milliliter(s) Soy Sauce
220 grams Udon Noodles
5 grams Roasted White Sesame Seeds
50 milliliter(s) Water for the Sauce
1 tbsp Honey

Heat a drizzle of oil in a frying pan on high heat.
Once hot, fry the beef mince and mushrooms, 5-6 mins.
Break up the mince as it cooks, then drain the fat. Season with salt and pepper. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw mince. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.
Meanwhile, peel and grate the garlic (or use a garlic press).

Add the spring greens and garlic to the frying pan.
Stir-fry, 1-2 mins.

Next, stir in the gochujang, soy, water and honey (see pantry for both). Simmer, 2-3 mins.
Add the udon noodles to the pan. Toss to coat, using a fork to gently separate them. Simmer until piping hot, 1-2 mins.
Add a splash of water if the sauce is too thick.

Share the noodles between your bowls.
Sprinkle with sesame seeds to finish.
Enjoy!